- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper deals with algebraic properties of type-forming operations.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper discusses distributivity principles.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is possible as the Lambek-Grishin calculus has been used in natural language processing and semantic parsing.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also possible as the paper deals with a formal grammar framework.
